\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 4. H. atriplicifolium} (Lam.) Spach, {\i Ann. Sci. Nat.} ser. 2 (Bot.), {\b 6}: 366 (1836). Erect, up to 150 cm. Leaves of non-flowering shoots 20-50 × 10-30 mm, rhombic-elliptical to ovate-lanceolate, obtuse, with 3 prominent veins, shortly petiolate; leaves of flowering shoots 10-40 × 10-20 mm, oblong-cordate, pinnate-veined, sessile; all with a dense covering of peltate scales and stellate hairs. Flowering branches elongate, rigid, leafless, densely tomentose and with patent, purplish, viscid hairs; flowers in lax cymes. Sepals 3; petals yellow, spotted at the base.{\i  C. & S. Spain.} Hs.
