\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. T. lignosa} (Sweet) Samp., {\i Bol. Soc. Brot.} ser. 2,{\b  1}: 128 (1922) ({\i T. vulgaris} Willk., {\i T. melastomatifolia} Grosser,{\i  Helianthemum tuberaria} (L.) Miller). Perennial up to 40 cm, with branched, woody stock bearing leaf-rosettes resembling those of{\i  Plantago} spp. Leaves 20-55 × 8-25 mm, obovate-lanceolate to elliptical, gradually narrowed at the base into an indistinct petiole, subglabrous (rarely hairy) above, tomentose or sericeous-pubescent beneath. Flowering stems 20-30 cm, unbranched. Bracts lanceolate, acute. Flowers c. 30 mm in diameter, 3-7, in bracteate cymes. Sepals 10-15 × 4-7 mm, lanceolate-acuminate. Petals unspotted. 2n = 14.{\i  Scrub and woodland. Iberian peninsula and W. Mediterranean region, extending to S.E. Italy.} Bl Co Ga Hs It Lu Sa Si.
